wicketText: Jofra Archer lbw b Bumrah 21 (15b 1x4 2x6 17m) SR: 140
commentary: That's that. Archer has been given lbw, but he's reviewed. India won't get the full-blown visceral celebration but know they've got this.. He went across, front foot at cover, as the low fully hit the back boot which was in front of middle. Was the angle taking it too far? Bat not close, so that's no issue. Hawk-Eye shows it'd go on to clip leg stump. Third final in ICC tournaments in a year for India!

wicketText: Rishabh Pant c †de Kock b Maharaj 0 (2b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0
commentary: is that two wickets in the over for Maharaj? Two wickets off the sweep? South Africa think so. The umpires are checking for a bump ball. Goes for the sweep against a very full ball, and ends up meeting it on the full, in fact, outside off. And he's a goner. Straight up in the air off the top edge of the toe end, and it balloons up behind him to de Kock. What a turnaround in the space of three balls, after India had run away to a flier

shortText: Arshdeep Singh to de Kock, no run
commentary: goes short now, angling down leg, and de Kock, looking to hook, is a little cramped for room. Misses, or did he get a little touch on this? Rishabh Pant thinks so, and India review the not-out decision. Was there a tiny nudge of glove on this? De Kock looks a little sheepish, but that's not too far from his usual expression. Nothing on Ultra Edge, and India lose their review
